=head1 DESCRIPTION

The shared access signature (SAS) configuration that allows DataSync to
access your Microsoft Azure Blob Storage.

For more information, see SAS tokens
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/datasync/latest/userguide/creating-azure-blob-location.html#azure-blob-sas-tokens)
for accessing your Azure Blob Storage.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Token => Str

Specifies a SAS token that provides permissions to access your Azure
Blob Storage.

The token is part of the SAS URI string that comes after the storage
resource URI and a question mark. A token looks something like this:

C<sp=r&st=2023-12-20T14:54:52Z&se=2023-12-20T22:54:52Z&spr=https&sv=2021-06-08&sr=c&sig=aBBKDWQvyuVcTPH9EBp%2FXTI9E%2F%2Fmq171%2BZU178wcwqU%3D>



